The Meta Ads API uses OAuth2 access tokens for authentication [1]. You must obtain a valid User, System User, or Page access token that includes the ads_management permission [2][1][3]. Tokens are passed in API requests via the access_token query parameter or the Authorization: Bearer <token> header [1]. When using the Facebook Business SDK for PHP, you initialize the API by providing your app ID, app secret, and access token as shown below [2][3].

```php
use FacebookAds\Api;

Api::init('<APP_ID>', '<APP_SECRET>', '<ACCESS_TOKEN>');
$api = Api::instance();
```
